      "type": "multiple_choice",
      "question": "What is the practical motivation for continuing pretraining on in-domain unlabeled text before supervised fine-tuning?",
      "stem_format": "plain_text",
      "choices_format": "plain_text",
      "choices": [
        "It can adapt the model's general language knowledge toward the target domain before labels are used.",
        "It replaces the need for a task-specific objective in all cases.",
        "It guarantees the model will forget all biases from pretraining.",
        "It turns a decoder-only model into a bidirectional encoder without changing architecture."
      ],
      "answer_index": 0,
      "explanation": "Domain-adaptive pretraining uses raw text from the target area to shift the model toward that distribution. Fine-tuning can then specialize on the labeled task from a better domain-specific initialization.",
